      • hasMoreFields

        public java.lang.Boolean hasMoreFields()
        Description copied from class: CharByteDataParser.InputConsumer
        A flag that indicates that the last consumed field should have completed a record and it did not, typically when encountered an unexpected delimiter (a field delimiter instead of a record delimiter). The method is supposed to return null if unknown.
        Overrides:
        hasMoreFields in class CharByteDataParser.InputConsumer
